text:
USS George HW Bush Launches Airstrikes Targeting Islamic State Storyful • 22 February 2017 Fighter jets from the USS George HW Bush conducted airstrikes targeting the Islamic State from the eastern Mediterranean Sea on Monday, February 13.
The aircraft carrier entered the Mediterranean on February 2, replacing the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower Carrier Strike Group in its efforts with Operation Inherent Resolve, the US’ operation to eliminate the Islamic State . Credit: US Navy via Storyful
